Take salt of Tartar vitriolated half a drachm;
                     Powder.
                   Cream of Tartar one drachm; white Sugar-candy two drachms; make it into a fine Powder for four Doses, which may be taken every morning and evening in white or Rhenish wine.

Take Cristals of Tartar two ounces; Scammony one ounce;
                     Troches.
                   white Sugar four ounces; with Gum Dragon dissolv'd in Rose-water as much as is sufficient; let it be made into Troches according to Art.

Take of choice Rhubarb two drachms; Cream of Tartar one drachm;
                     Purging Infusion.
                   infuse them in four ounces of Endive-water for a night;




then strain it and add Syrup of Roses solutive, Syrup of Cicory with Rhubarb, of each half an ounce, Cinamon-water two drachms; give it in the morning fasting: This Electuary is also an excellent Cholagogue.

Take the Pulp of Damask-prunes ten ounces;
                     Electuary.
                   Powder of Scammony, Cream of Tartar, of each two ounces, Rhubarb ten drachms, Cinamon half an ounce; yellow Sanders two drachms; the best Manna, Syrup of Cicory with Rhubarb, of each eight ounces; mix all together into an Electuary according to Art.

Take of Barley-water two pints;
                     Tincture.
                   Red-rose-buds one ounce; spirit of Vitriol twenty drops, or as much as is sufficient to make it of a good Tincture, let it infuse all Night, then strain it, and add Syrup of Jujubes four ounces; mix it, and give three or four spoonfulls every three hours.

Take of sweet Almonds one ounce; the four greater Cold-seeds of each half an ounce;
                     Emulsion.
                   white Poppy-seeds two ounces; let the Almonds be blanched, and all well beaten in a stone Mortar; then with four pints of Barley-water, make an Emulsion; strain it, and add Syrup of the Juice of Limmons, Diacodium, of each three ounces; Cinamon-water two ounces; of which let the sick drink often, four spoonfulls at a time.

Take the Waters of Lettice, Water-lillies of each two ounces;
                     Julep.
                   Syrup of red Poppies one ounce; Cinamon-water half an ounce; Laudanum opiatum four grains; Oil of Vitriol six drops; mix it, and give four spoonfulls of it to cause sleep.


                     Oil.
                  Take Chymical-oils, of Juniper-berries, Turpentine, Spike, of each half an ounce;




Oils of Chamomel, Earth-worms, Rue, Foxes, of each one ounce; Spirit of Castor two drachms; mix it.

Take of Treacle-water, Fennel-water, of each one ounce;
                     Cordial to cause Sweat.
                   Syrup of Peony, Syrup of the Juice of Scurvigrass, of each half an ounce; Antimony Diaphoretick, Bezoar mineral, Crabs-eyes in powder, of each ten grains; Laudanum opiat. four grains; Tincture of Castor one drachm; Oil of Cloves three drops;




Spirit of Salt Armoniack ten drops; mix it, and let the sick take it, being well cover'd with cloths, whereby the sweat will the easier come forth.

Take Extract. Rudii, pil. ex duobus, of each one drachm;
                     Purging Pills.
                   Mercury dulcis half a drachm; Oil of Cloves four drops; mix them for three Doses.

When much bloud is voided by coughing, there is great danger;
                     Sputum Sanguinis.
                   wherefore we must hasten the more to its cure; lest the opportunity here (if any where urgent) be lost by delay; for the singular substance of the Lungs is easily infected and corrupted, but difficultly restor'd and repair'd; wherefore bloud carried down from the Head into the Lungs, and raising a Cough, is to be stopt in its efflux.


Take of Plantane, Housleek, Wood-sorrel, of each two handfulls;
                     Decoction.
                   boil them in Barley-water one quart till half of it be boiled away, then strain it, and add Syrup of Jujubes three ounces; Salt prunella one drachm; Spirit of Niter twenty drops; mix it, and give four spoonfulls every three hours.

The Apertion may be made four or five inches from the Sternon;
                     Caution.
                   not so near the upper as the lower rib, because under each rib there is an Intercostal Vein, Arterie and Nerve.

The Hectick Fever is called in Greek 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , i. e. ab habitu;
Febris Hecticae.
quod in habitu corporis, vel in partibus solidis consistat.

But here the Sex is to be consider'd, the Female not so well enduring this evacuation;
                     Cautio.
                   because Emeticks cause great Commotions, and flatuous Vapours in them; which may also prevent or corrupt natures own intentions in her great discharge of turgent humours.

This Poison must not be sent out by vomiting or purging;
                     Cure.
                   neither is phlebotomy allowed.


Take Tincture of Red-roses, Barley-water, of each twelve ounces;
                     Julep.
                   Cinamon-water two ounces, Syrup of Violets three ounces, Salt Prunella two drachms; mix it, and give the sick three spoonfulls every two hours.

If hunger be suddenly diminish'd by Choler, either over fat, or abounding in plenty;
                     Cure.
                   it may commodiously be evacuated by an Antimonial Emetick. Many other proper Medicines are set down in the 8th. and 9th. pages.

Take pil. foetidae, ex duobus, of each fifteen grains; Oil of Harts-horn four drops;
                     Purging Pills.
                   make it into Pills; take them in the Morning fasting.

Take the Roots of Marsh-mallows two ounces;
                     Clyster.
                   of Mallows, Marsh-mallows, Mullein, of each two handfulls; the Seeds of Anise, Sweet-fennel, Coriander, Flax, Faenugreek, of each two ounces; let them be cleansed, bruised and boiled in a quart of Spring-water till half be consumed, then strain it, and add oil of white Lillies, the Fat of a Hen, of each one ounce; mix it for a Clyster▪

Take of sweet Almonds blanched, white Poppy-seeds, of each two ounces;
                     Emulsion.
                   French-barley boiled four ounces; the waters of Fennel, Plantain, Roses, of each half a pint; Barley-water a pint, let it be made an Emulsion; to which add Syrup of Violets three ounces; confectio Alkermes de Hyacintho, of each two drachms; Laudanum twenty grains; Spirit of Niter forty drops; mix it.

Take the Waters of Fennel, Fumitory, Sorrel, Succory, of each three ounces;
                     Julep.
                   Cinamon-water, distill'd Vinegar, Syrups of Violets and white Poppies, of each two ounces;




                  Laudanum opiatum ten grains; Spirit of Niter twenty drops; mix it.

Take the Powder of Jallop, Cinamon, of each fifteen grains;
                     Purging Powder.
                   Powder of Rhubarb tosted half a drachm; mix it

Take the Waters of Plantain, Comfry, of each two ounces;
                     Cordial Julep.
                   Cinamon-water half an ounce; Syrup of Mirtles one ounce; Confectio de Hyacintho, Diascordium, of each one drachm; Laudanum opiat. four grains; mix it.

Take new Milk wherein Steel hath been quenched one pint;
                     Clyster.
                   Honey of Roses one ounce; Venice Turpentine half an ounce; the Yelk of one Egg; Balsam of Sulphur four drops; mix it.

Take of Hemp-seed two ounces;
                     Opiate.
                   Soap two drachms; bruise the seed, and boil it in half a pint of new Milk, till half of it be consumed; then strain it, and add Syrup of Saffron half an ounce; tincture of Saffron two drachms; Laudanum opiatum four grains; mix it, and give half of it in the morning fasting, and the remainder at night, going to bed.


                     Electuary.
                  Take of Conserves of Scurvigrass, three ounces; Confectio Alkermes, half an ounce;




Powder of Crabs-eyes, two drachms; Flowers of Salt Armoniack, Tarter vitriolated, of each half a drachm; Spirit of Castor one drachm; Oil of Cloves twenty drops; mix it, and give two drachms morning and evening.

Take of pil. foetidae, ex duobus, of each half a drachm;
                     Purging Pills.
                   Amber, prepar'd Steel, Borax, Mercur. Dulcis, of each one scruple; Mirrh, Castor, Saffron, of each twelve grains; Oil of Cloves, Spirit of Salt Armoniack, of each six drops; make it into ten Pills for two doses, which may be taken in the Morning fasting.

All long Hemorrhagies of Bloud are dangerous, especially those of the Womb;
                     Progn.
                   If it be caused by exulceration, and be in elderly Women, 'tis incurable.

Take the Roots of Satirion and Eringo candied, of each one ounce;
                     Electuary.
                   candied Ginger and preserv'd Nutmegs, of each two drachms;




Kernels of Hazle-nuts and Fistick-nuts, of each half an ounce; Powder of a Bull's-pizle, of Ivory, Seeds of Rocket, Bishops-weed, of each one drachm; Species Diambrae, Diamosc. dulcis, of each six drachms; Confectio Alkermes one ounce and half; with Syrup of the juice of Citrons; make it into an Electuary according to Art.

Take of Cinamon, Rhubarb, Anise-seed, of each two drachms;
                     Purging Infusion.
                   let them be bruised,




and infused in four ounces of Plantain-water very hot, for the space of a Night, then strain it, and add Syrup of Succory with Rhubarb, the best Manna, of each half an ounce; mix it, and give it in the Morning fasting.

The signs of hard Labour are easily known;
                     Signs.
                   if the Child do stir, and there be strong pains, and no water appear, the Secundine is strong.

Wherein the force of concreting or growing together of Stones (in divers parts of the Body) consists, is not enough known;
                     Cause of the Stone.
                   I will freely declare what I conjecture in this obscure matter, whereby I may (according to my power) the more help others (that are ingenious) to search out this hidden truth.


Take of Extractum Rudii, one scruple;
                     Purging Pills.

                  Mercur. dulcis, Salt Armoniack, of each half a scruple; make it into four Pills, and take them in the Morning.


Take of Verdigreece, and common Salt, of each two ounces;
                     Ointment.
                   powder them, and calcine them together; then mix it with eight ounces of Vnguentum Enulatum.

Take the Water of the Spawn of Frogs four ounces; Honey of red Roses one ounce;
                     Injection.
                   white Troches of Rhasis one drachm; powder the Troches, and mix all together for an Injection.

Take of Mercur. dulcis six grains;
                     Purging Bolus. 
                  Diagredium, Rezin of Jallop, of each three grains; with Syrup of Roses solutive, make it into a Bolus; give it in the morning fasting.
